{"cursor":"2518","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Everyday image = caption = poster director = Michael Winterbottom\n| producer = Laurence Bowen writer = starring = John Simm Shirley Henderson\n| music = Michael Nyman cinematography = Sean Bobbitt editing = distributor =\n| Channel 4 released = runtime = 106 minutes country = United Kingdom language =\n| English budget =\n}} 'Everyday' is a British drama film directed by Michael Winterbottom. Known\nduring its lengthy production variously as Seven Days and then Here and There,\nthe film stars John Simm as a man imprisoned for drug smuggling and charts his\nrelationship with his wife, played by Shirley Henderson. http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/exclusive-domestic-\nposter-for-michael-winterbottoms-trishna-starring-freida-pinto-20120518\n\nWritten by Winterbottom and Laurence Coriat, the film was shot a few weeks at a\ntime over a five-year period from 2007 to 2012 to reflect the protagonist's time\nin prison and achieve an authentic aging process. Everyday premiered at the\nTelluride Film Festival on 3 September 2012 http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/telluride-review-michael-\nwinterbottoms-everyday-is-uneven-long-but-emotionally-rewarding-20120903\nand then screened at the Toronto International Film Festival on 8 September\n2012. http://tiff.net/filmsandschedules/tiff/2012/everyday The film\nwas produced by Britain's Channel 4 http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a393317/channel-4-reveals-201213-\ndrama-lineup-john-simm-gabriel-byrne-more.html and premiered in the UK on\ntelevision on 15 November\n2012, http://www.channel4.com/programmes/everyday later released\ntheatrically on 18 January 2013. At the Stockholm International Film\nFestival in November the film was awarded the FIPRESCI-Award.\n","linknr":128,"url":"Everyday_(film)","recorded":1374548702,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Everyday_(film)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Everyday_(film)&action=edit","//